metadata.name: Distant Views #13
metadata.description:
This work explores generative way of painting landscapes on canvas. Algorithm uses backward moves with big polygon brush to produce mountain-like structures. Shades of randomly selected color make illusion of distance and adds to diversity of terrain. Sun and Moon can have different positions on the horizon or not be visible at all. Their color changes depending on the position. Besides night and day, there are three rough variants of composition based on percentage that sky takes on canvas. There is a also chance to have snowy mountain on top.

Artwork was created using p5js.

@VolatileMoods

December, 2021.

metadata.name: Visa to the stars #255
metadata.description:
Generative space scenes with an illustrative look.

Use the capture functions to export in big after opening it in its own window, the artwork is full of details.

Press SPACE to show/hide the menu

Control the camera and explore the scene with :
- Mouse Left : Rotate
- Mouse Right : Pan
- Mouse Middle : Zoom

I wrote an article about the project, with a technical breakdown of the piece at https://ulucode.com/wp/visa-to-the-stars/


Decent GPU REQUIRED, you can tune the performances with the "Quality" setting in the menu.
Better performances with Chrome.

Keyboard shortcuts:
SPACE : show/hide menu
A : toggle anti-aliasing
C : take a capture of the ccurrently selected resolution
R : reset camera position/orientation
S : display stats
P : pause animation

metadata.name: Lust I #3
metadata.description:
LUST is about the pure joy of creating. Through play, imagination and simplicity. Lust is a minimalistic generative art project divided in three releases (I,II,III). 

The project is based on the algorithm Gravity, used in my previous releases.

metadata.name: Klimtiche #102
metadata.description:
Inspired by the 'Tree of Life' by Gustav Klimt.
Every bird comes with a default weather setting but all weather is optional.
On the keyboard:
use 's' to make it snow
use 'w' to make wind blow
use 'r' to make it rain
use 'n' to stop the animation and then again to clear all animation. 
Variables are snow intensity, rain intensity, wind speed and palette.
Made in p5.js, every tree / meadow / sky is unique in design.
Two birds is rare.
Monochrome is rare.

April 2022, Hungary

Features

Number of rings
Detail of noise

Keyboard control
----------------
[f] toggle fullscreen and hide cursor
[space] manually generate new composition
[a] automatically generate new composition
[s] save image

Touchscreen
-----------
Tap left edge to automatically or right edge to manually generate a new composition.

metadata.name: Pandora #174
metadata.description:
Pandora received many gifts from the Gods: beauty, flattery, kindness, skill, grace, intelligence, but also the art of deception and seduction. They gave her the name Pandora (Πανδώρα), “endowed with all the gifts” in Greek.

The Pandora generative series has the same qualities as the mythological figure. Able to adopt many different shapes, a wide variety of colors and styles, all created from simple rules.

Only one thing though, do not open the box.

[S] key to save a PNG image
Press once for a resolution of 2000x2000, a second time for a resolution of 4000x4000, then 6000x6000 and finally 8000x8000

Made with p5.js

Artist: Estienne
April 2022
License: NFT 2.0

metadata.name: Unsquare composition #1
metadata.description:
Inspired by Jazz, Unsquare composition I experiments with the notion of non-squared rhythmic forms, where freedom and improvisation take as a premise the idea of an imperfection where we can also find harmony. 

Please do not expect perfect results.
